GANG violence erupted outside the Bellville Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Monday after arguments between rival gangsters, who pulled out guns and fired at each other.The shootout, which sources say is linked to a bigger gang battle, happened just outside the court building.Gang shootings have recently flared up in various hot spots around Western Cape.While some sources say a gang member was shot in Monday's violence, police said no one was wounded.Police spokesperson Captain FC van Wyk said several gang members had appeared in the court on Monday in several cases. &ldquo;At about 10am arguments between gangster groupings arose outside the court building,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;They then pulled out firearms and shot at each other. This happened just outside the court building.&rdquo;The gunmen ran away after the shots were fired and no arrests were made.&ldquo;The situation is currently under control. SAPS members are still at the scene gathering information," Van Wyk said.It is understood members of the Terrible Josters gang, as well as the rival Bad Boys and Sexy Boys gangs were involved in the violence.It is understood a prominent gang member with links to the 28s was among those who appeared in the Bellville court on Monday.About 28 alleged gang members were arrested in Ravensmead last week in an operation clamping down on gangsterism.The prominent gang member linked to the 28s was among those taken into custody.